msg: Transferred from the Adobe Open Source Subversion Repository
New effects, as requested by Thermo (and which made sense for SDK effects as well):
Wait: This effect waits for either/both a timeout period and a specified event. useful for choreographing Effect sequences.

CallFunctionAction: When played, this effect calls a specified function with an optional list of parameters. Again, useful when choreographing multiple effects in a sequence, where a function might be called after/before specific effects are played.

Also, tweaked NumberInterpolator to clamp start/end values to the supplied start/end values, rather than depending on floating-point precision to round off correctly in the parametric calculation of the proper result.
